{"id":455936,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frank_M._Robinson","text":"e=\"preserve\">Frank Malcolm Robinson (August 9, 1926 \u2013 June 30, 2014) was an American science fiction and techno-thriller writer, editor and screenwriter. His best known novel was \"The Power\". In the 1970s, he was a speechwriter for gay politician Harvey Milk, before he was murdered in 1978.\nRobinson was born in Chicago, Illinois. He was openly gay. He had a small role in the movie \"Milk\" (2008) about Harvey Milk, starring Sean Penn.\nRobinson died on June 30, 2014 in San Francisco, California, aged 87.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Americans","surface_form":"American","offset":76},{"uri":"Science_fiction","surface_form":"science fiction","offset":85},{"uri":"Techno","surface_form":"techno","offset":105},{"uri":"Thriller_(genre)","surface_form":"thriller","offset":112},{"uri":"Writer","surface_form":"writer","offset":121},{"uri":"Editor","surface_form":"editor","offset":129},{"uri":"Screenwriter","surface_form":"screenwriter","offset":140},{"uri":"Novel","surface_form":"novel","offset":169},{"uri":"The_Power_(novel)","surface_form":"The Power","offset":180},{"uri":"Public_speaking","surface_form":"speechwriter","offset":215},{"uri":"Politician","surface_form":"politician","offset":236},{"uri":"Harvey_Milk","surface_form":"Harvey Milk","offset":247},{"uri":"Chicago","surface_form":"Chicago","offset":313},{"uri":"Illinois","surface_form":"Illinois","offset":322},{"uri":"Gay","surface_form":"gay","offset":346},{"uri":"Movie","surface_form":"movie","offset":378},{"uri":"Milk_(movie)","surface_form":"Milk","offset":385},{"uri":"Sean_Penn","surface_form":"Sean Penn","offset":426},{"uri":"San_Francisco","surface_form":"San Francisco","offset":471},{"uri":"California","surface_form":"California","offset":486}]}